                        <item>Backup, <idno>TS 1055</idno>, from <date when="2006-03-08"/> (copy of Neg.
                           847).</item>
                     </list>
                  </surrogates>
               </additional>
               <msPart n="1">
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 I</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem n="1" class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="1r" to="13r">1r-13r</locus>
                        <textLang mainLang="da"/>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>Notes taken in the <name type="org" key="BibNatFr">Bibliothèque
                              nationale de France</name> and <name type="org" key="BibSaiGen">Bibliothèque Sainte-Geneviève</name> in <name type="place" key="Paris01">Paris</name>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <extent>18. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height>176</height>
                                 <width>113</width>
                              </dimensions>
                           </extent>
                           <foliation>The first four leaves are glued together but they are foliated
                              in pencil 1-4. The following five leaves are blank and are not
                              foliated. It is unknown when the first four leaves were glued
                              together, but since the text is crossed over it is possible that <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name> himself glued
                              them together.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>Nr 1</q> (in black
                           ink) and <q>Paris</q>(in blue crayon) are found. </p>
                        <p>In the middle of the cover the title of the volume <q>Biblioteker <lb/>
                              og <lb/> håndskriftsamlinger <lb/> i <lb/> Paris.</q> is written in
                           black ink and underlined in red crayon.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
               <msPart n="2">
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 II</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem n="2" class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="14r" to="35r">14r-35r</locus>
                        <textLang mainLang="da"/>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <rubric>Tyskland=Østerrig</rubric>

                        <note>Notes made in <date when="1885"/> concerning various libraries
                           including <name type="place" key="BerGer01">Berlin</name>, <name type="place" key="Pra01">Prague</name>, <name type="place" key="WieAus01">Wienna</name>, <name type="place" key="MunGer01">Munich</name>, <name type="place" key="FraGer01">Frankfurt am
                              Main</name>, and <name type="place" key="Wolfen01">Wolfenbüttel</name>.</note>
                        <note>Includes copies of text samples from various manuscripts in German
                           repositories made with carbon paper.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <extent>61. (1 + 9 + 43 + 7 + 1). <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height max="229">229</height>
                                 <width max="180">180</width>
                              </dimensions>
                           </extent>
                           <foliation>Only the written leaves are foliated in pencil. The outermost
                              leaves are made of cardboard and serve as the cover of the notebook.
                              The front cover is foliated as 14, while the back cover is blank and
                              therefore not foliated.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>Nr 2</q> is written
                           in black ink.</p>
                        <p>In the top right corner the stamp <q>Kr. Kålund</q> is found.</p>
                        <p>In the middle of the cover the title of the volume <q>Tysklan=Ørserig</q>
                           is written in black ink.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <origin>The date <origDate when="1885">1885</origDate> appears in various
                        places in the manuscript. </origin>
                  </history>
               </msPart>

               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 III</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="37r" to="49v">37r-49v</locus>
                        <textLang mainLang="da"/>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>Descriptions made in <date when="1902">1902</date> and <date when="1904">1904</date> of manuscripts in German collections, for
                           example in <name type="place" key="BerGer01">Berlin</name>, <name type="place" key="Kiel01">Kiel</name> and <name type="place">Lübeck</name>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <support><material>Paper</material>.</support>
                           <extent>20. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height atLeast="167" atMost="223">167-223</height>
                                 <width atLeast="52" atMost="180">52-180</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only written leaves are foliated.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>Nr 3 a</q> is
                           written in black ink.</p>
                        <p>In the middle of the cover the title <q>Håndskriftbeskrivel[se]</q> is
                           written in blue crayon. Below <q>Tyskland</q> is written in grey
                           pencil.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <origin> The date <origDate when="1904">Juli 1904</origDate> is attested in
                        various places throughout the manuscript. </origin>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 IV</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="50r" to="57r">50r-57r</locus>
                        <textLang mainLang="da"/>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes on Codex Erfordensis</title>
                        <note>The notes were used in Kristian Kålund's publication <bibl><ref target="KriKal1909a">Codex Erfordensis af de Lundske annaler</ref>,
                                 <biblScope unit="pages">303-309</biblScope></bibl>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <support><material>Paper</material>.</support>
                           <extent>26 (1 + 24 + 1). <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height atMost="220">220</height>
                                 <width atMost="180">180</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only the written leaves are foliated in pencil. The outermost
                              leaves are made of a different paper and serve as the cover of the
                              notebook. The front cover is foliated as 50, while the back cover is
                              blank and therefore not foliated.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>Nr. 3b</q> is
                           written in black ink. </p>
                        <p>In the middle of the cover the title of the volume <q>Codex Erfordensis
                              23, 9vo (Annales Lundenses)</q> is written in black ink. Above the
                           title <q>Kiel</q> is written in pencil, and below the title <q>Cf. Arkiv
                              f. nord. filol.| XXV. 303 ff.</q> is written in pencil.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 V</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="58r" to="105r">58r-105r</locus>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>Notes on manuscripts held in Swedish and Norwegian repositories. Among
                           these, a letter to <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian
                              Kålund</name> from <name type="person" key="CarPet001">Carl af
                              Petersens</name> and copies of text samples from various manuscripts
                           made with carbon paper, are found.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <support><material>Various types of paper</material>. </support>
                           <extent>53 leaves in various sizes: <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height atLeast="28" atMost="229">28-229</height>
                                 <width atLeast="80" atMost="183">80-183</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only the written leaves are foliated in pencil. The outermost
                              leaves are made of a different, thicker paper and serve as the cover
                              of the notebook. The front cover is foliated as 58, while the back
                              cover is blank and therefore not foliated.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>I</q> is written;
                           and in the lower part of the cover the signature <q>Nr 4a</q> is
                           found.</p>
                        <p>In the middle of the cover the title of the volume <q>Sverig-Norge</q> is
                           written. Both signatures and the title are written in black ink.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 IV b</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="106r" to="178r">106r-178r</locus>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>A detailed description of <ref target="#HolmPerg04-0022-is">Holm.
                              Perg. 22 4to</ref></note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="unknown">
                           <extent>74 + 38 leaves (two notebooks). <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height atLeast="111" atMost="178">111-178</height>
                                 <width atMost="67" atLeast="112">67-112</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only the written leaves are foliated in pencil. </foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the stamp <q>J. L. Wisbech Skindberg
                              31, Bog &amp; Papir handel</q> is found. In the middle of the cover
                           the title of the volume <q><ref target="#HolmPerg04-0022-is">Stockh. isl.
                                 perg. 22, 4to.</ref></q> is written, and in the lower part of the
                           cover the signature <q>Nr 4b</q> is written. Both the title and the
                           signature are written in black ink. </p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 VI</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="179r" to="189v">179r-189v</locus>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>A detailed description of DG: 34-36.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <support><material>Paper</material>. </support>
                           <extent>12. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height>232</height>
                                 <width>181</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only written leaves are foliated in pencil.</foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>This part does not have any cover or signatures.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
               <msPart>
                  <msIdentifier><altIdentifier type="partial">
                     <idno>Acc. 36 VI</idno>
                  </altIdentifier></msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="notes handfr">
                        <locus from="190r" to="221v">190r-221v</locus>
                        <title type="supplied">Notes</title>
                        <note>Notes on manuscripts in the <name type="org" key="AdvLib">Advocates
                              Library</name> and the <name type="org" key="Britmus">British
                              Museum</name> (now the manuscript collection is transferred to the <name type="org" key="BL">British Library</name>).</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <objectDesc form="codex">
                        <supportDesc material="chart">
                           <support><material>Paper</material>.</support>
                           <extent>34. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height atLeast="61" atMost="228">228</height>
                                 <width atLeast="89" atMost="183">183</width>
                              </dimensions>.</extent>
                           <foliation>Only the written leaves are foliated in pencil. </foliation>
                        </supportDesc>
                     </objectDesc>
                     <handDesc>
                        <handNote scope="sole" script="other" scribe="KriKaa001">Written by <name type="person" key="KriKaa001">Kristian Kålund</name>.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <bindingDesc>
                        <p>In the top left corner of the cover the signature <q>Nr 5</q> is written
                           in black ink. In the middle of the cover the tile
                           <q>Håndskriftoptegnelser fra <lb/> Advocates library &amp; British
                              Museum.</q> is written.</p>
                     </bindingDesc>
                  </physDesc>
               </msPart>
